        <h3 data-uuid="5dccfd6f66e942e59b2ba8dabc247d72">Reaction to Lincoln’s Call</h3>
        <p data-uuid="d37714a9917b49408881f280b2e767e4"> The fall of Fort Sumter stunned the North. Lincoln declared the South to be in a state of rebellion and asked state governors for 75,000 militiamen to put down the rebellion. States now had to choose: Would they secede, or would they stay in the Union? Democratic senator Stephen Douglas, speaking in support of Lincoln’s call for troops, declared, “There can be no neutrals in this war, <i>only patriots</i>—or <i>traitors</i>.”<br />
        </p>
